# Documentation & Research

When implementing features, debugging, or answering questions, **consult official sources first** — do not guess Fiber/CKB protocol behavior or RPC shapes.

Use `WebFetch`, `WebSearch`, or uploaded docs before writing code or giving definitive answers.

## When to Look Things Up

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Fiber RPC methods, types, payment flows | Read [Fiber Docs](https://www.fiber.world/docs) and [RPC API Reference](https://www.fiber.world/docs) |
| JS/TS integration, `FiberSDK`, channels/invoices | Read [JavaScript SDK](https://www.fiber.world/docs/build/sdk/js) — prefer `@ckb-ccc/fiber` patterns |
| CKB on-chain context, cells, scripts, RPC | Read [CKB Docs](https://docs.nervos.org/docs) |
| UI/UX patterns, similar tools, hackathon inspiration | Browse [Fiber Showcase](https://www.fiber.world/showcase) |
| TypeScript style, types, declarations | Read [W3Schools TS Best Practices](https://www.w3schools.com/typescript/typescript_best_practices.php) and [TS Handbook: Do's and Don'ts](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/declaration-files/do-s-and-don-ts.html) |
| Unclear errors, version mismatches, edge cases | Search Fiber docs FAQ/Troubleshooting sections before improvising fixes |
| Hackathon scope, category fit, submission requirements | Read [Gone in 60ms announcement](https://talk.nervos.org/t/gone-in-60ms-fiber-network-infrastructure-hackathon-announcement/10418) and CKBoost campaign rules |
| VS Code extension (`apps/vscode`) — commands, views, manifest, publishing | Read [VS Code Extension API](https://code.visualstudio.com/api) and relevant guides before implementing |

